<div class='allCommunityAnswers'>
<div class='communityAnswer'>
<div class='communityAnswerBody'>
<div class='answererUserIcon'>
<a class="leftAlignedImage userPhoto" href="/user/show/114403318-hannah-nolan"><img alt="" src="https://s.gr-assets.com/assets/nophoto/user/u_100x100-259587f1619f5253426a4fa6fb508831.png" /></a>
</div>
<div class='communityAnswerTextContainer'>
<span class='communityAnswererName'>
<a href="/user/show/114403318-hannah-nolan">Hannah Nolan</a>
</span>
<span class='communityAnswerText'>
<span class="expandableContainer"><span class="truncatedContent">Santiago named the novel &quot;When I Was Puerto Rican&quot; to depict her identity issues between being from and growing up in Puerto Rico, then having to immi<a class="jsShow showAction" href="#">…more</a></span><span class="fullContent">Santiago named the novel "When I Was Puerto Rican" to depict her identity issues between being from and growing up in Puerto Rico, then having to immigrate to the United States and assimilate into American culture. Throughout her assimilation, she feels as if she is losing her Puerto Rican identity and becoming a different person, hence the past tense phrasing. There actually is a video on her Youtube channel of her own explanation of the title, <a target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow" href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=ZiQLSRTyUIY">https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=ZiQLS...</a><a class="jsHide hideAction" href="#">(less)</a></span></span>
</span>
</div>
</div>
