<div id="review_1371919039" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1371919039" />
    <a title="Farha Hasan" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/16946971-farha-hasan"><img alt="Farha Hasan" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1474538287p2/16946971.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1371919039?book_show_action=true">Aug 23, 2015</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Farha Hasan" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Farha Hasan" href="/user/show/16946971-farha-hasan">Farha Hasan</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1371919039" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer2464920605434231490">I love immigrant stories and this was very inspirational. Most of the book focuses on the author&apos;s early years in Puerto Rico. It would have been nice to have some back story on her parents and their relationship, but she may not have had that information. The book ends when she gets accepted into the School of Arts in Manhattan which is when I think her life would have just started getting interesting. We know later on she gets a scholarship to Harvard.</span>
  <span id="freeText2464920605434231490" style="display:none">I love immigrant stories and this was very inspirational. Most of the book focuses on the author's early years in Puerto Rico. It would have been nice to have some back story on her parents and their relationship, but she may not have had that information. The book ends when she gets accepted into the School of Arts in Manhattan which is when I think her life would have just started getting interesting. We know later on she gets a scholarship to Harvard.</span>
  <a data-text-id="2464920605434231490" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


