        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer749942955" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer4585615448220144324">3.5 stars.<br/>This is an interesting memoir, but it does feel old school. Most memoirs I read are much more in-your-face, even graphic. This tale of poverty and immigration is more subtle and slow moving. I loved the descriptions of Puerto Rico and her confusion about her parents&apos; love-hate relationship.<br/>Glad I read it.</span>
  <span id="freeText4585615448220144324" style="display:none">3.5 stars.<br />This is an interesting memoir, but it does feel old school. Most memoirs I read are much more in-your-face, even graphic. This tale of poverty and immigration is more subtle and slow moving. I loved the descriptions of Puerto Rico and her confusion about her parents' love-hate relationship.<br />Glad I read it.</span>
