  <span id="freeText17295181493041402613" style="display:none">This book was a very interesting book to read. It's a true story about the life of Esmeralda Santiago who was born and raised in Puerto Rico. She was a liitle girl who went through a hard time growing up. Her family was really poor and she had a lot of siblings. She sometimes had to cook for her family and even takae care of her siblings. Her father cheated on her mother and soon Esmeralda found out that she had a sister from her dad's side who was close to the same age as her and livesd with her mother in New York City. Esmeralda sometimes felt that her parents sometimes didn't care about her and she felt that every time a new sibling was born the further away she was getting from being loved by her parents. Her life goes on and she becomes a writer.</span>
